RabbitMQ doesn't automatically propagate W3C trace context like HTTP does. You need to manually inject/extract the context via message headers.

**Service A (Publisher) — inject context:**

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into headers
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;
    props.Headers["tracestate"] = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Service B (Consumer) — extract and link context:**

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");

// In your consumer callback:
void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    ActivityContext parentContext = default;

    if (ea.BasicProperties.Headers != null
        && ea.BasicProperties.Headers.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw))
    {
        var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
        ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentContext);
    }

    // Start a new activity linked to the producer's context
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "OrderEvent Process",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext);  // <-- this is the key link

    // … process the order
}
```

**Wire it up in `Program.cs` (both services):**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());               // Jaeger, Zipkin, etc.
```

**Why this works:** `traceparent` carries the trace ID + parent span ID per the [W3C Trace Context](https://www.w3.org/TR/trace-context/) spec. By passing `parentContext` to `StartActivity`, the consumer's span becomes a child of the producer's span — giving you one continuous trace across the queue.

**If you use MassTransit or NServiceBus**, they do this injection/extraction automatically — you'd just need to register their OpenTelemetry source (e.g., `AddSource("MassTransit")`).
